---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Sheet from '../../components/Sheet.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import facts from '../../content/facts';

const chromeStoreUrl = 'https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/verso/celmibcnighdegjjcipimmdkjikhkdjm';

const demo = facts.sheetCode;
const isDraft = !demo;
---

<Layout
  title="Verso for Code — See what a second model writes"
  description="AI models generate different code for the same prompt. Verso shows you both implementations before you ship."
  ogTitle="Verso for Code"
  ogDescription="The model wrote your function. Another model would have written it differently."
  noindex={isDraft}
  includeScrollReveal
  includeSheet={!!demo}
>

<Nav variant="consumer" />

<header class="vs-hero">
  <div class="vs-wrap vs-hero-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="vs-eyebrow vs-rise"><em></em><span class="vs-mono">Code</span></div>

      <h1 class="vs-h1 vs-rise">
        <span class="rec">Another model</span>
        <span class="rec">would have</span>
        <span class="ver">written it differently</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="vs-lede vs-rise">
        You ask a model to write a function. It picks an approach, uses a library, handles
        edge cases one way. A second model writes <b>different code for the same prompt</b>.
        One of them has a bug you won't find until production. Verso shows you both.
      </p>

      <div class="vs-actions vs-rise" id="install">
        <a class="vs-btn" href={chromeStoreUrl}>
          Add to Chrome
          <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 13 13" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M1 12L12 1M12 1H4M12 1v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <span class="vs-note"><b>Free.</b> Works on ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    {demo && (
      <Sheet
        front={{
          label: 'Model A',
          side: 'Recto',
          questionPrefix: 'You asked:',
          question: demo.question,
          answer: demo.modelA.answer,
          answerMark: demo.modelA.mark,
          closing: demo.modelA.closing,
          flipCue: 'Turn the page',
          verdict: '1 of 2',
        }}
        back={{
          label: 'Model B',
          side: 'Verso',
          questionPrefix: 'Same question:',
          question: demo.question,
          answer: demo.modelB.answer,
          answerMark: demo.modelB.mark,
          closing: demo.modelB.closing,
          flipCue: 'Turn back',
          verdict: demo.verdict,
        }}
      />
    )}
  </div>
</header>

<section class="vs-band" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="vs-marquee">
    <p>
      <span>One uses recursion</span><span>The other iterates</span><span>Same spec, different bugs</span><span>Only one handles the edge case</span>
      <span>One uses recursion</span><span>The other iterates</span><span>Same spec, different bugs</span><span>Only one handles the edge case</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vs-steps" id="how">
  <div class="vs-wrap">
    <div class="vs-shead vs-rise">
      <span class="vs-mono">Why it matters</span>
      <h2>Code generation is the most expensive place to trust one answer.</h2>
      <p>A wrong product recommendation wastes money. Wrong code wastes days. One model picks a recursive solution that blows the stack on large inputs. Another uses iteration but misses a null check. A third imports a library you've never heard of. The differences aren't cosmetic — they're architectural decisions that compound. Seeing a second implementation before you commit to the first is the cheapest code review you'll ever get.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vs-steplist">
      <div class="vs-step vs-rise">
        <span class="vs-stepnum">STEP 01</span>
        <h3>Install once</h3>
        <p>Verso opens as a side panel next to ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity. Nothing to configure.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-step vs-rise">
        <span class="vs-stepnum">STEP 02</span>
        <h3>Write code normally</h3>
        <p>Ask your model to generate functions, debug errors, or architect systems. Verso watches for prompts where a second implementation matters.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-step vs-rise">
        <span class="vs-stepnum">STEP 03</span>
        <h3>Read the other implementation</h3>
        <p>Your prompt goes to a second model. Two implementations, side by side. Different approaches surface different trade-offs — before either one reaches production.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vs-trans" id="data">
  <div class="vs-wrap vs-transgrid">
    <div class="vs-rise">
      <span class="vs-mono">The deal</span>
      <h2>Verso is free because <u>preference is worth something.</u></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="vs-rise">
      <p>Every time you pick one code implementation over another, you answer a question every AI lab wants answered: which model writes code that developers actually use. We collect your prompts, both answers, and your preference. We sell the measurement — not the conversations.</p>

      <a class="vs-labslink" href="/what-we-collect">
        Read exactly what we collect and what we sell
        <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 13 13" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M1 6.5h11M7.5 2l4.5 4.5L7.5 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vs-close">
  <div class="vs-wrap vs-rise">
    <h2>Get a <u>second implementation.</u></h2>
    <p>One click, one second opinion. The cheapest code review is seeing what another model writes for the same prompt.</p>
    <a class="vs-btn" href={chromeStoreUrl}>
      Add to Chrome — free
      <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 13 13" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M1 12L12 1M12 1H4M12 1v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"/>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<Footer links={[
  { href: '/', label: 'Extension' },
  { href: '/what-we-collect', label: 'What we collect' },
  { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
  { href: 'mailto:contact@tryverso.ai', label: 'Contact' },
]} />

</Layout>
